-- Hindustan Zinc Profit Unexpectedly Drops on Lead, Zinc Prices
-- B y   A b h i s h e k   S h a n k e r
-- 2012-01-20T11:01:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/hindustan-zinc-profit-unexpectedly-drops-on-lead-zinc-prices.html
Hindustan Zinc Ltd. (HZ) ,  India â€™s largest
producer, reported an unexpected decline third-quarter profit
following a drop in the prices of lead and zinc.  Net income fell to 12.7 billion rupees ($252 million), or
3.01 rupees a share, in the three months ended Dec. 31 from 12.9
billion rupees, or 3.05 rupees, a year earlier, the unit of
London-based  Vedanta Resources Plc (VED)  said today in a statement to
the Bombay Stock Exchange. The median of 28 analyst estimates
compiled by Bloomberg was 13 billion rupees. Sales increased 5.8
percent to 27.5 billion rupees.  Zinc, required to rust-proof steel, averaged 18 percent
lower at $1,916 a ton in the quarter, while lead fell 20 percent
to $2,009 a ton in  London . The average spot price of silver, the
precious metal the company also produces, jumped 20 percent to
$31.80 an ounce.  Shares of Udaipur, Rajasthan-based Hindustan Zinc rose 0.4
percent to 126.80 rupees in Mumbai. The benchmark Sensitive
Index increased 0.6 percent.  Total expenses gained 24 percent to 15.4 billion rupees in
the period on higher royalty and fuel prices. Raw material costs
rose to 1.16 billion rupees from 460.5 million rupees a year
earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
